I generated Baseline Profiles and saw promising results in my Macrobenchmark test:
[![enter image description here](https://i.sstatic.net/awf2H.png)](https://i.sstatic.net/awf2H.png)

I put the baseline-prof.txt file in the main folder next to the Manifest.xml.
When I run the app in release mode I cannot see a visible difference when performing the action I generated the baseline profile for.

Can I only see the benefit of baseline profiles when installing the app via Google Play store? Am I missing something?

Also what do those P50, P90, P95 mean?
The docs say:
“These measurements are collected in distribution: 50th, 90th, 95th, and 99th percentile.”

Not sure what that means

